76", "dates": ["1776"], "description": ["Hand colored. Relief shown pictorially. Shows administrative divisions. Insets: A chart of the mouth of Hudson's River, from Sandy Hook to New York.--A plan of the city of New York.--Plan of Amboy, with its environs, from an actual survey. Scale ca. 1:650,000. LC Maps of North America, 1750-1789, 1045 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. Vault AACR2: 100; 651/1; 651/2; 651/3; 651/4; 651/5; 651/6; 651/7; 651/8; 700/1; 710/2"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:40:09.708Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-12", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-12"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/74692880/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd380/g3800/g3800/ct000082.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd380/g3800/g3800/ct000082.gif#h=381&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd380:g3800:g3800:ct000082/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=2017&w=794", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd380:g3800:g3800:ct000082/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=4035&w=1589"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new york (state)", "canada", "qu\u00e9bec", "perth amboy", "new york", "new jersey", "northeastern states", "united states", "qu\u00e9bec (province)", "new york city"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["74692880", "2025-06-07t18:30:16.200000", "2005-01-04t16:52:50"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["catalog", "american revolution and its era: maps and charts of north america and the west indies, 1750-1789", "geography and map division", "military battles and campaigns"], "score": 34.2189, "shelf_id": "G3800 1776 .P6", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["administrative and political divisions", "new york (state)", "canada", "new york (n.y.)", "early works to 1800", "perth amboy", "new york", "new jersey", "northeastern states", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "united states", "qu\u00e9bec (province)", "maps"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:14:20.380Z", "title": "The provinces of New York and New Jersey; with part of Pensilvania, and the province of Quebec", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/74692880/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2006625921", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2006625921/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/13f8e8ec-e3f5-51b7-b1a1-5c0d6c9331e8", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3814p.ct006952", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3814p.ct006952/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["baker (lithographer : new york, n.y.)", "brinley, francis w."], "date": "1836", "dates": ["1836"], "description": ["General street map showing buildings and lot lines. Relief shown by hachures. Depths shown by soundings. Also covers part of Raritan Bay. LC copy imperfect: Upper left corner torn away, laminated, mounted on cloth backing to form single sheet, fold-lined, small sections missing at fold lines, sheet trimmed, annotated in ink to show additional buildings and names. Includes inset \"Map shewing the situation of Perth Amboy with New York, the Atlantic Ocean &c., scale 3 miles to an inch\". Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:40:12.234Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2006625921/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ct006952.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ct006952.gif#h=150&w=100", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ct006952/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1337&w=894", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ct006952/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=2675&w=1788"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["perth amboy", "raritan bay", "new york", "new jersey", "perth amboy region", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2016-10-03t09:58:45", "sheet", "2006625921", "2025-06-07t01:46:57.300000"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["catalog", "cities and towns", "geography and map division"], "score": 34.2189, "shelf_id": "G3814.P4 1836 .B7", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["real property", "raritan bay (n.j. and n.y.)", "bathymetric maps", "perth amboy", "raritan bay", "new york", "perth amboy region (n.j.)", "new jersey", "perth amboy region", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "united states", "maps"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:51:03.749Z", "title": "Map of the city of Perth Amboy, N.J. : February 1836", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2006625921/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/gm71000984", "http://www.loc.gov/item/gm71000984/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/e3e24845-78ac-5814-bd0b-74b6c33051a6", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3814p.ar125000", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3814p.ar125000/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1780", "dates": ["1780"], "description": ["\"The map presented here shows the city and harbor of Charleston, South Carolina, at the time of the first British siege of Charleston and attack on Fort Sullivan in June 1776. This was the earliest British attempt to capture Charleston during the Revolutionary War, by which General Henry Clinton and Admiral Sir Peter Parker sought to put down the rebellion in the southern colonies. Above the map of Charleston is a view of Fort Sullivan, where William Moultrie, a colonel in the state militia of South Carolina, repulsed a British attack. The fort was later renamed Fort Moultrie in his honor. After failing to secure Charleston, the British fleet sailed to New York City. British forces would not return to Charleston until 1780. The map also includes an inset view of Amboy (present-day Perth Amboy) on the Raritan River, in New Jersey. It shows a layout of the town with houses, streets, fields, vegetation, connecting roads, nearby parts of Raritan Bay and Staten Island, and the ferry to South Amboy. This map has a watermark. Relief is shown by hachures. The map is from the Rochambeau Collection at the Library of Congress, which consists of 40 manuscript maps, 26 printed maps, and a manuscript atlas that belonged to Jean-Baptiste-Donatien de Vimeur, comte de Rochambeau (1725-1807), commander in chief of the French expeditionary army (1780-82) during the American Revolution. Some of the maps were used by Rochambeau during the war. Dating from 1717 to 1795, the maps cover much of eastern North America, from Newfoundland and Labrador in the north to Haiti in the south. The collection includes maps of cities, maps showing Revolutionary War battles and military campaigns, and early state maps from the 1790s.\" World Digital Library."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:45.215Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/gm71000984/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ar125000.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ar125000.gif#h=150&w=220", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ar125000/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=464&w=681", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ar125000/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=929&w=1363"], "index": 7, "language": ["french"], "location": ["south carolina", "charleston", "perth amboy", "charleston harbor", "new jersey", "united states", "fort moultrie"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["gm71000984", "2025-09-24t13:14:18.100000"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["american revolution and its era: maps and charts of north america and the west indies, 1750-1789", "military battles and campaigns", "world digital library", "catalog", "france in america", "geography and map division", "rochambeau map collection"], "score": 34.2189, "shelf_id": "G3814.P4 1780 .P5", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["south carolina", "fort moultrie (s.c.)", "fort moultrie", "charleston", "maps", "charleston harbor (s.c.)", "aerial views", "early works to 1800", "perth amboy", "early maps", "siege", "new jersey", "charleston harbor", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "charleston (s.c.)", "united states", "history"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:36:27.580Z", "title": "[Plan d'Amboy]. [Vues de la rade de Charles-Town et de Fort Sulivan, mai 1780]", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/gm71000984/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529947/1908050202/0270.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_basil_ver02:data:sn85035720:00279529947:1908050202:0269/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529947/1908050202/0270.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-05-02/ed-2/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529947/1908050202/0270.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_basil_ver02:data:sn85035720:00279529947:1908050202:0269/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "